               <p>BENJAMIN POLE PRICE. I am a <rs id="t18280911-224-viclabel1144" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-224-victim1282 t18280911-224-viclabel1144"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18280911-224-crimeloc1145">Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-224-crimeloc1145" type="placeName" value="Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-224-crimeloc1145" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-224-off1142 t18280911-224-crimeloc1145"></join>. On the 18th of August, I lost some braces from my door-post, but I did not see them taken - I saw them in the possession of the officer, and knew them to be mine.</p>
               <p> - LAWRENCE. I was at a friend's house, opposite the prosecutor's; I saw the prisoner walk backwards and forwards; he then took the braces, and went off - the watchman stopped him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-224-person1283">
                  JAMES 
                  CONNOLLY
               <interp inst="t18280911-224-person1283" type="surname" value="CONNOLLY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-224-person1283" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-224-person1283" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the cry of Stop thief! I proceeded to the spot, and stopped the prisoner, who was in the act of dropping these braces.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182809110132"></xptr>Prisoner's Defence. This gentleman came and took me; when he was at the watch-house he said he did not see me take the braces - I know nothing about them.</p>
